`javelin-ext/` implements a code-generated, obligation-stack steno
dictionary as a drop-in replacement for the enumerable outlineâ†’definition
dictionary format, and validates it against a Rust reference
implementation. Depending on this subtree gets you `StenoGeneratedDictionary`,
a `StenoDictionary` subclass whose `Lookup()` reconstructs definitions at
query time from rule tables instead of a stored map, keeping firmware
footprint small.

The walker (`.cc`) and its public wrapper (`.h`) are tightly coupled to
`steno_generated_dictionary_data.h` (not in this directory but generated
alongside it): the `CONSTRUCTS`/`TYPES` arrays there define all behavior,
so any generator change to that data changes lookup results immediately
without touching this subtree's source. `test_main.cc` closes the loop by
replaying golden stroke sequences (from `build-javelin`, via generated
`steno_generated_testdata.h`) through the same `Lookup()` entry point and
diffing against the Rust walker's recorded verdicts â€” this is the
authoritative correctness check for the whole subtree, since the walker's
64-stroke/8KB arena limits mean truncation failures are silent and only
caught here.

Invariant spanning the subtree: `test_main.cc` is fully compiled out
(`#if JAVELIN_EXT_RUN_TESTS`) in firmware builds, so production binaries
never link the test harness or its `Console` stub; only `.h`/`.cc` ship.
Both the walker and the dictionary header avoid console machinery
entirely to preserve this.